This paper deals with the problem of classifier evasion, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically in the subfield of adversarial machine learning. The paper focuses on tree ensembles, which are commonly used in tasks such as image classification and object recognition, suggesting that the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
